==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Detent
<hw>De*tent"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧tente</ets>, fr. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧tendre</ets> to unbend,
relax; pref. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧-</ets> (L. <ets>dis-</ets> or <ets>de</ets>)
+ <ets>tendre</ets> to stretch. See <er>Distend</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Mech.)</fld> <def>That which locks or unlocks a movement; a catch,
pawl, or dog; especially, in clockwork, the catch which locks and
unlocks the wheelwork in striking.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>detente</ent>⟦br⟧
